s Installation</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://community.1and1.com\">1&amp;1 Community</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:22:\"Daniel Alves de Jesus.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1949:\"<p>If you have migrated your WordPress website, switched to a new domain or created a local copy for testing, chances are you will need to update links to point to your new location. You can easily change this with the <a title=\"open Plugin website in a new window\" href=\"http://wordpress.org/plugins/search-and-replace/\" target=\"_blank\">Search &amp; Replace</a> plugin.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Go to the admin area of your WordPress installation by entering the respective URL in your browser.</li>\n<li>Install the <strong>Search &amp; Replace</strong> plugin.</li>\n<li>Under the name of the plugin you have just installed, click <strong>Settings</strong>.</li>\n<li>Enter the URL of your &#8220;previous WordPress installation&#8221; in the <strong>Search for</strong> field.</li>\n<li>Activate the <strong>All &#8211; search and replace!</strong> option.</li>\n<li>Enter the URL of your new WordPress installation in the <strong>Replace with</strong> field.<br />\nFor a local copy it could look something like this: http://localhost/<strong>wp-testenvironment/</strong></li>\n<li>Click <strong>Go</strong>.<br />\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1397\" src=\"https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/url-ersetzen-01_en.png\" alt=\"Replacing URL\" width=\"918\" height=\"476\" srcset=\"https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/url-ersetzen-01_en.png 918w, https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/url-ersetzen-01_en-300x155.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 918px) 100vw, 918px\" /><br />\nThe changes are being applied.</li>\n<li>Click <strong>Settings &gt; Permalinks</strong>.</li>\n<li>Select <strong>Post name</strong> and click <strong>Save Changes</strong>.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://community.1and1.com/fixing-broken-links-wordpress/\">Fixing Broken Links of a WordPress Installation</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://community.1and1.com\">1&amp;1 Community</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:63:\"https://community.1and1.com/fixing-broken-links-wordpress/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"1\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:4;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:45:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:33:\"WordPress 4.7.4  Update Available\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:44:\"https://community.1and1.com/wordpress-4-7-4/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:53:\"https://community.1and1.com/wordpress-4-7-4/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s: